text: Epsilon Piscis Austrini, also known as ε Piscis Austrini, is a blue-white star in the constellation of Piscis Austrinus. It can be seen with the naked eye and has an apparent visual magnitude of +4.17. The system is located about 400 light years from the Sun and has an annual parallax shift of 8.0981 ± 0.3582 mas as seen from the GAIA satellite. == References == Category:Stars
title: Epsilon Piscis Austrini
